HEADWORD: De facto
<hw>De` fac"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L.]</ety> <def>Actually; in
fact; in reality; <as>as, a king <ex>de facto</ex>, -- distinguished
from a king <ex>de jure</ex>, or by right</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

